<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CAB: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - RESERVOIR AND/OR PUMP MOTOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>RESERVOIR AND/OR PUMP MOTOR</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600750">Figure 50</hotlnk>for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600750" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600750" filename="../figg16/G1600750.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Reservoir and Pump Motor</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. 4000, 8000 ONLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. NOZZLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PUMP TO WIPER NOZZLE HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RESERVOIR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. PUMP MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MOTOR TO GROUND WIRE</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. PANEL SWITCH TO MOTOR WIRE</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. WIRING HARNESS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and tilt hood assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect pump to wiper nozzle hose (Item 2) from pump motor outlet fitting.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connector from pump motor (Item 4).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Since two different types of pump motor and reservoir assemblies (Items 3 and 4) may be
                    found on cabs, always check Parts Catalog before disassembling pump motor (Item 4) from reservoir
                    (Item 3). If pump motor is detachable, pull pump motor from reservoir.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the reservoir-to-cowl mounting screws and lift complete pump, motor (Item 4) and
                    reservoir (Item 3) from cowl.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600750">Figure 50</hotlnk>for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If pump motor (Item 4) was removed, place pump motor in position in reservoir (Item 3)
                    and secure with screws. Use new seal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector to pump motor (Item 4).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect pump to wiper nozzle hose (Item 2) to pump motor outlet fitting.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill reservoir, check operation and close and latch hood assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Be sure an ample supply of windshield washer solvent is maintained in reservoir to insure
                        satisfactory operation of windshield washer.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
